author: Observer Sport
title: England sink Wales in thriller with Elliot Daly’s flying finish | Sport
text:
England dug deep to maintain Eddie Jones’s winning run as their head coach, coming from behind to win a dramatic Six Nations match against Wales in Cardiff. Trailing 16-14 with four minutes left, England capitalised on a clearance from Jonathan Davies that went straight down the middle to George Ford in space. A wide pass sent the ball to Eliot Daly on the left, who ran a flat line and seared past Alex Cuthbert and into the corner. Owen Farrell nailed the conversion to give England a 21-16 win.
Earlier, Liam Williams had scored the home side’s try, to help them to a 13-8 half-time lead. Ben Youngs had scored England’s first try.
Paul Rees’s match from the Principality Stadium to follow
